<br>
There is a creature, invisible and intangible, that lurks in norrath. It is found everywhere large groups of people gather. It causes people to move slowly. It even causes people to black out and disappear. It is called lag. Normally it only affect a small amount of people, but for what you are considering, it will be our weapon. You will all enter Ak'Anon to find multitudes of defenders waiting for you. We will not raise a sword against you, nor will we cast magics harmlessly at you. But our mere prescence will invoke this demon called lag, and it will come, putting emphasis on the death of Linkdeath.<br>
<br>
And you will be its victims. Where you will be attacked by those Ak'Anon defenders commonly refered to as NPC's, they are immune to Lag. And they will shred your bodies to pieces. So I do not recommend you bind your soul in Ak'Anon, for they love to keep shredding any enemy of Ak'Anon.<br>
<br>
 We have already conversed with the gods known as Verant. We cannot help our npc defenders, nor can we attack you en mass. We also are not allowed to block the entryway into our city. But we have the right to stand around and watch you get slaughtered when you cant even move to get out of your own way. I bid you not to partake in this, an egotistical tier'dal's maniacal attempt at honor.<br>
<br>
So Baron Apep, he who has little wisdom. Bring forth your armies for slaughter. For it will be you who is ultimately responsible for their misfortune. All based on your pitiful excuse of a vendetta. You want to make everyone suffer for one person's crime. A crime against your wife, who wouldn't be in this predicament had you been a more civilized Tier'dal to begin with. If you want to point fingers on who is to blame, point them at yourself, for being the kind of loatheful person you are.<br>
<br>
 Charizma married you for love, but did you tell her about the social stigma she would suffer because of you? Did you tell her how many people you have made into enemies? Did you tell her just how bad her life was going to be because you are so intolerant of other people that you are ostracized by many? Did you even think that she would lose friends because of you? No, I guess not. Because you really only care about yourself, dont you?<br>
<br>
And for Charizma, I am truly sorry that my attacks against your husband will pain you, and may even cause you to dislike me. But he has gone too far and I cannot stand for it any longer. We all wear rose-colored glasses, but his lenses are cracked and he will not get them fixed.<br>
<br>
Xianya Lilboomer<br>
