First it was at your marriage to the fair Charizma, where I learnt that the greatest forces in Norrath are hate and love. While I don't believe I am worthy yet to have those words tattoed on the knuckles of my hands; I applaud you for being so enlightened as to be unable to distinguish between the two.<br>
<br>
And now there is the attack on Ak'anon. As you are a noble amongst a noble race, I am forced to reconsider my hatred of my step-brother Prince Bragnar. What I mistook for the childish temper tantrums of a young dog were actually the signs of his nobility. <br>
<br>
I have much to learn, for that reason I will observe the goings on in King Ak'anon's throne room, and hopefully become more enlightened.<br>
<br>
I offer you thanks for the lessons you have taught me, and only wish I had more than words to offer in return. But as I have only words, I offer this:<br>
<br>
Should you succeed in penetrating Ak'anon's defenses, congratulations. You will have succeeded where all of clan Grikbar has failed. You will have elevated the status of Ebon Storm, and indeed all of the Tier'dal, above that of the kobolds of Steamfont.<br>
